                "abstract": "© 2022 The Author(s) 2022. Published by Oxford University Press. All rights reserved. For permissions, please e-mail: journals.permissions@oup.com.Motivation: Read-merging algorithms that look solely at the reads can misalign and mis-merge the reads (especially near repetitive sequences). Results: The C++ program ProSynAR has been written to take the reads' position in the reference into account when performing (and deciding whether to perform) a merge. Availability: ∗Nix users can retrieve the source from GitHub (https://github.com/Benjamin-Crysup/prosynar). Windows binary available at https://github.com/Benjamin-Crysup/prosynar/releases/download/1.0/prosynar.zip.",
